  "prompt": "What does dark humor mean?",
  "response": "Dark humor, also known as black humor, is a style of comedy that finds humor in subjects that are typically considered serious, taboo, or distressing. This can include topics such as death, illness, tragedy, or moral dilemmas. Dark humor often aims to provide a sense of relief or a different perspective on uncomfortable or grim situations, but it can also provoke strong reactions, as not everyone appreciates jokes about sensitive subjects. The effectiveness of dark humor often relies on the context and delivery, as well as the audience's sensibilities.",
